[Malaria transmission is perfectly possible in Singapore and
asymptomatic carriers visiting Singapore could be the source of
infection. With prompt case recognition and treatment and the rigorous
vector control in Singapore it is unlikely that there will be a larger
outbreak. - Mod.EP
